            <h3>Ask Your Healthcare Provider</h3>
            <p>Is your healthcare provider not using <mark>https://</mark> for their sites? That means you have <em>no privacy</em> when searching for your medical concerns! Your employer, internet provider, or neighbor on your WiFi can easily see whatever you're looking for.</p>
            <p>Ask your healthcare provider to protect your privacy by enabling <mark>https://</mark> for all their sites.</p>
            <p>Don't just stop with your doctors &mdash; Is your work e-mail missing two-factor? Ask them why. Is your IT department still using Internet Explorer? Ask why they haven't offered a <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/a/answer/3019558?hl=en&ref_topic=3062034&rd=1" target="_blank">more secure option</a>.</p>
